          <p xml:id="Kali127-kilavi">ituvumatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en"></p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="Kali127">
                <l>teriyiṇar ñāḻalun tēṅkamaḻ puṉṉaiyum </l>
                <l>puriyaviḻ pūviṉ kaitaiyuñ ceruntiyum </l>
                <l>variñimi ṟimirntārppa viruntumpi yiyaipūtac </l>
                <l>cerumiku nēmiyāṉ ṟārpōlap peruṅkaṭal </l>
                <l>varimaṇal vāycūḻum vayaṅkunīrt taṇcērppa;</l>
                <l rend="space">koṭuṅkaḻi vaḷaiiya kuṉṟupōl vālekkar </l>
                <l>naṭuṅkunōy tīraniṉ kuṟivāyttā ḷeṉpatō</l>
                <l>kaṭumpaṉi yaṟaluku kayalērkaṇ paṉimalka </l>
                <l>viṭumpaiyō ṭiṉaipēṅka vivaḷainī tuṟantatai;</l>
                <l rend="space">kuṟiyiṉṟip paṉṉāṇiṉ kaṭuntiṇṭēr varupataṅkaṇ</l> 
                <l>ṭeṟitirai yimiḻkāṉa letirkoṇṭā ḷeṉpatō</l>
                <l>vaṟivaña ruḻantēṅki yāynalam vaṟitākac </l>
                <l>ceṟivaḷai tōḷūra vivaḷainī tuṟantatai</l>
                <l>kāṇvara viyaṉṟavik kaviṉpeṟu paṉittuṟai </l>
                <l>yāmattu vantuniṉ kuṟivāyttā ḷeṉpatō</l>
                <l>vēynala miḻantatōḷ viḷaṅkiḻai poṟaiyāṟṟāḷ </l>
                <l>vāṇutal pacappūra vivaḷainī tuṟantatai;</l>
                <l rend="space">ataṉāl, </l>
                <l>iṟaivaḷai nekiḻnta vevvanō yivaṭīra </l>
                <l>vuravukkatir teṟumeṉa vōṅkutirai viraiputaṉ </l>
                <l>karaiyama laṭumpaḷit tāaṅ </l>
                <l>kuravunīrc cērppa varuḷiṉai yaḷiyē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l corresp="5">O man from the coast of glowing cool waters that surround areas of lined sand</l>
                <l corresp="4">by the big sea like the garland on the much-fighting discus bearer,</l>
                <l corresp="1">while on clear-clustered Ñāḻal trees, Puṉṉai trees fragrant with honey,</l>
                <l corresp="2">screwpine trees with powers opening in strands and pear trees</l>
                <l corresp="3">striped bees hum [and] roar, while dark bees gorge themselves in harmony,</l>
                <l>Does that she reached your sign so that [her] shivering pain ended</l>
                <l>by a pure dune like a hill enveloped by curved backwaters speak</l>
                <l>about your abandoning her while she laments, desperate with sorrow</l>
                <l corresp="6-9">so that tears well up in [her] eyes that resemble carps that shed fierce dew in the black sand? </l>
                <l>Does her receiving [you] in the seashore grove buzzing with dashing waves</l>
                <l>after looking for the moment your fast firm chariot comes, many days, without a sign, say</l>
                <l>about your abandoning her while the tight bangles creep over [her] arms</l>
                <l corresp="10-13">so that [her] choice beauty becomes vain, lamenting, bearing knowing sorrow?</l>
                <l>Does her reaching your sign, coming at midnight</l>
                <l>to this beautiful chilly ghat where she advanced to come to see, say</l>
                <l>about your abandoning her while pallor creeps up [her] bright forehead,</l>
                <l corresp="14-17">she unable to bear the burden of the shining jewels in [her] shoulders that lost [their] bamboo beauty?</l>
                <l corresp="18">Therefore,</l>
                <l>so that her troubling pain ends in which the bangles come loose on [her] wrists,</l>
                <l>like the high wave in a hurry take care of the densely growing Aṭumpu</l>
                <l>on its shore, thinking the strong rays [of the sun] will burn [it],</l>
                <l corresp="19-22">o man of the coast of strong water, you care [for her], being one was considerate [before].</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
